
Design a modern virtual learning platform and school management system called ThinkDifferent Virtual School with the school motto:
“To Infinite Learning and Beyond.”
The platform should support online education for Kenyan and international learners and accommodate multiple curricula including:
Kenya 8-4-4 system (Form 3 and Form 4)
Competency Based Curriculum (CBC) from Grade 1 to Junior Secondary
IGCSE-style international learning
The system should be secure, scalable, mobile-friendly, and cloud-based, supporting Google Meet or similar video learning integrations.
1. Student Admission & Registration Module
Create a Learner Registration System with the following fields:
Primary Key: Registration Number (auto-generated)
Fields:
Registration Number (Auto-generated)
Full Name (as it should appear on certificate)
Gender
Phone Number
Email Address
Date of Birth
Place of Residence
Passport Photo Upload
Level of Education / Current Grade
2. Emergency Contact / Guardian Information
Each student must provide guardian or parent details.
Fields:
Emergency Contact ID (Primary Key)
Student Registration Number (Foreign Key)
Parent / Guardian Full Name
Phone Number
Relationship to Student
Example:
Father
Mother
Guardian
Sponsor
3. Payment Management System
Include a school fees payment module.
Fields:
Payment ID (Primary Key)
Student Registration Number (Foreign Key)
Date of Payment
Amount Paid
Payment Method (M-Pesa, Bank, Card)
Payment Reference
Fee Structure:
Monthly Fee: KSh 1500
3-Month Offer: KSh 3500
System features:
Payment history
Fee balance tracking
Payment confirmation
Receipt generation
4. Teacher / Volunteer Registration
Teachers may join as online volunteer tutors.
They will be compensated KSh 500 per hour.
Teacher registration fields:
Primary Key: Teacher ID
Fields:
Full Name
Gender
Phone Number
Email
TSC Number
Subject Specialization
Professional Description / Bio
Availability Schedule
Years of Experience
5. Online Class Attendance System
Students joining a class must sign the digital register.
Features:
Register only active during class time
Timestamp when student joins
Teacher attendance dashboard
Attendance statistics
Late entry tracking
6. Online Examination System
The platform must include an online examination module.
Features:
Digital exams and quizzes
Automatic grading
Result generation
Performance analytics
Exam output:
Marks
Mean score
Subject averages
Student ranking
Performance trends
7. Report Form Generation
Generate digital report forms including:
Student Name
Registration Number
Subjects
Scores
Average
Grade
Teacher Remarks
Principal Remarks
Term performance summary
Also include:
Class statistics
Performance graphs
8. Subject Registration for National Exams
Create a KNEC exam registration module.
Students will select their intended national exam:
Options:
KCSE
Qualifying Exams
Equation
KJSEA
KPSEA
Required fields:
Registration Number
Exam Type
Entry Code
First Attempt
Repeater (All Subjects)
Repeater (Partial)
Birth Certificate Number
National ID Number
Parent Name
Parent Phone Number
9. Career Pathways Guidance
Include a Career Advisory Section to guide students after completion.
Topics:
University pathways
Technical & vocational careers
Entrepreneurship
Digital careers
Scholarship opportunities
Mentorship programs
10. Meet the Team Section
Create a leadership profile section including:
Founder Co-founders Academic Director Technology Director Volunteer Teachers
Each profile should include:
Photo
Name
Title
Biography
Vision for education
11. Photo Gallery
Create a gallery section showing:
Virtual classes
Student achievements
Online graduations
Teacher activities
School events
12. Dashboard & Analytics
Admin dashboard should show:
Total students enrolled
Active classes
Teacher statistics
Fee payments
Attendance rate
Exam performance
Growth statistics
13. Security Features
Include:
Secure login
Student/Teacher/Admin roles
Encrypted personal data
Audit logs
Two-factor authentication
14. Technology Stack Suggestion
The system may be built using:
Frontend: React / Flutter
Backend: Node.js / Django
Database: PostgreSQL / MySQL
Video Integration: Google Meet / Zoom API
Payment: M-Pesa integration
15. School Identity
School Name: ThinkDifferent Virtual School
Motto: “To Infinite Learning and Beyond.”
Mission: Provide accessible, flexible, and technology-driven education that empowers learners to succeed academically and globally.
